fields.title: Sum of Two Numbers
fields.description: Given two non-negative integers separated by a space, return their sum. For example, if the input is '2 3', the output should be '5'.

fields.title: Reverse a String
fields.description: Given a string consisting only of alphabets, return the reversed string. For example, input 'hello' should produce output 'olleh'.
fields.constraints: Input string length between 1 and 100; letters only.

fields.title: Find Maximum in List
fields.description: Given a list of integers separated by spaces, return the maximum number in the list.
fields.constraints: List contains between 1 and 100 integers, each between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Check Palindrome
fields.description: Determine if a given string is a palindrome. A palindrome reads the same backward as forward.
fields.constraints: String length between 1 and 100, containing only alphanumeric characters.

fields.title: Fibonacci Number
fields.description: Given an integer n, return the nth Fibonacci number. The sequence starts with 0, 1, 1, 2, ...

fields.title: Calculate Factorial
fields.description: Given a non-negative integer n, return its factorial. Factorial of n (n!) is the product of all positive integers less than or equal to n.

fields.title: Prime Number Checker
fields.description: Determine if a given number is prime. Return 'True' if prime, otherwise 'False'.
fields.constraints: Input integer will be between 2 and 10000.

fields.title: Compute GCD
fields.description: Given two integers, return their Greatest Common Divisor (GCD).
fields.constraints: Integers are positive and less than 10000.

fields.title: Compute LCM
fields.description: Given two positive integers, return their Least Common Multiple (LCM).
fields.constraints: Integers are positive and less than 10000.

fields.title: Binary to Decimal
fields.description: Convert a binary number (given as a string) to its decimal representation.
fields.constraints: The binary string will be non-empty and contain only '0' and '1'.

fields.title: Decimal to Binary
fields.description: Convert a given decimal number to its binary representation (as a string).
fields.constraints: 0 <= number <= 1000

fields.title: Sort Array of Integers
fields.description: Given a list of integers, return the sorted list in ascending order.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100, each integer between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Find Second Largest Number
fields.description: Given a list of integers, find and return the second largest number in the list.
fields.constraints: The list contains at least two distinct integers.

fields.title: Count Vowels in a String
fields.description: Given a string, count and return the number of vowels (a, e, i, o, u) in the string.
fields.constraints: String length between 1 and 200, case insensitive.

fields.title: Check for Anagram
fields.description: Given two strings, check if they are anagrams of each other. Two strings are anagrams if they contain the same characters in a different order.
fields.constraints: Strings will be of equal length and contain only lowercase alphabets.

fields.title: String Compression
fields.description: Given a string, compress it by replacing sequences of the same character with the character followed by the count. For example, 'aaabb' becomes 'a3b2'.
fields.constraints: String length between 1 and 100; case sensitive.

fields.title: Unique Characters
fields.description: Given a string, determine whether all characters in the string are unique.
fields.constraints: String length between 1 and 100; assume ASCII characters.

fields.title: Merge Two Sorted Arrays
fields.description: Given two sorted arrays, merge them into a single sorted array.
fields.constraints: Arrays are sorted in ascending order. Combined length up to 200.

fields.title: Find Missing Number
fields.description: Given an array containing n distinct numbers taken from 0 to n, find the one number that is missing from the array.
fields.constraints: Array length is n; numbers are in the range [0, n].

fields.title: Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters
fields.description: Given a string, find the length of the longest substring without repeating characters.
fields.constraints: String length between 0 and 1000.

fields.title: Balanced Parentheses
fields.description: Given a string containing only the characters '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']', determine if the input string is valid. An input string is valid if: Open brackets are closed by the same type of brackets, and open brackets are closed in the correct order.
fields.constraints: String length between 1 and 100.

fields.title: Sum of Array Elements
fields.description: Given an array of integers, return the sum of its elements.
fields.constraints: Array size between 1 and 100, each element between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Calculate Average
fields.description: Given a list of numbers, calculate and return the average value.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; numbers can be integers or floats.

fields.title: Area of a Circle
fields.description: Given the radius of a circle, calculate its area using the formula A = πr². Assume π = 3.14.
fields.constraints: Radius is a positive number not greater than 100.

fields.title: Temperature Converter (Celsius to Fahrenheit)
fields.description: Convert a temperature given in Celsius to Fahrenheit using the formula F = (C × 9/5) + 32.
fields.constraints: Temperature in Celsius will be between -100 and 100.

fields.title: Find the Median
fields.description: Given a list of numbers, find and return the median value. If the list has an even number of elements, return the average of the two medians.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; numbers can be integers or floats.

fields.title: Most Frequent Element
fields.description: Given a list of integers, return the element that appears most frequently. If there are multiple, return any one of them.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100, each element between 0 and 100.

fields.title: Binary Search
fields.description: Given a sorted array of integers and a target value, implement binary search to find the index of the target. Return -1 if not found.
fields.constraints: Array is sorted in ascending order; size between 1 and 100.

fields.title: Matrix Transpose
fields.description: Given a matrix (2D array), return its transpose.
fields.constraints: Matrix dimensions up to 10x10.

fields.title: Spiral Order Traversal of Matrix
fields.description: Given a matrix, return all elements of the matrix in spiral order.
fields.constraints: Matrix dimensions up to 10x10.

fields.title: Anagram Checker
fields.description: Given two strings separated by a space, determine whether they are anagrams of each other. Two strings are anagrams if they contain the same characters in a different order.
fields.constraints: Both strings are of equal length and contain only lowercase letters.

fields.title: Balanced Brackets
fields.description: Check if a string of brackets is balanced. A balanced string has matching opening and closing brackets in the correct order.
fields.constraints: The string contains only '(', ')', '{', '}', '[' and ']'.

fields.title: Sort Integers
fields.description: Given a list of integers separated by spaces, return the list sorted in ascending order.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; integers range between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Find First Duplicate
fields.description: In a given list of integers, find the first duplicate element. If no duplicate exists, return -1.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 50; integers are between 1 and 100.

fields.title: Reverse Words in Sentence
fields.description: Given a sentence, reverse the order of words and return the resulting sentence.
fields.constraints: Sentence up to 200 characters; words separated by spaces.

fields.title: Longest Word Finder
fields.description: Find and return the longest word in a given sentence.
fields.constraints: Sentence up to 200 characters; words are separated by spaces.

fields.title: Word Count
fields.description: Count the number of words in a given sentence.
fields.constraints: Sentence up to 200 characters.

fields.title: Remove Vowels
fields.description: Remove all vowels from a given string and return the resulting string.
fields.constraints: String up to 100 characters; consider both uppercase and lowercase vowels.

fields.title: Factorial Calculator
fields.description: Calculate the factorial of a given non-negative integer n.

fields.title: Nth Fibonacci Number
fields.description: Return the nth Fibonacci number. The sequence starts with 0, 1, 1, 2, ...

fields.title: Prime Checker
fields.description: Determine if a given number is prime.
fields.constraints: Number between 2 and 10000.

fields.title: Merge Sorted Arrays
fields.description: Merge two sorted arrays into a single sorted array.
fields.constraints: Arrays are sorted in ascending order; total elements up to 200.

fields.title: Binary Search
fields.description: Perform binary search on a sorted array to find the index of a target element. Return -1 if not found.
fields.constraints: Array sorted in ascending order; size between 1 and 100.

fields.title: GCD Calculator
fields.description: Calculate the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of two integers.
fields.constraints: Both numbers are between 1 and 1000.

fields.title: LCM Calculator
fields.description: Calculate the Least Common Multiple (LCM) of two integers.
fields.constraints: Both numbers are between 1 and 1000.

fields.title: Celsius to Fahrenheit Converter
fields.description: Convert a temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit using the formula F = (C × 9/5) + 32.
fields.constraints: Temperature in Celsius between -100 and 100.

fields.title: Armstrong Number Checker
fields.description: Determine if a given number is an Armstrong number. An Armstrong number is equal to the sum of its own digits each raised to the power of the number of digits.
fields.constraints: Input number between 1 and 10000.

fields.title: Count Digits
fields.description: Count the number of digits in a given integer.
fields.constraints: Number is between 0 and 10^9.

fields.title: Sum of Array Elements
fields.description: Calculate the sum of all elements in a list of integers.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; each integer between -1000 and 1000.

fields.title: Product of Array Elements
fields.description: Calculate the product of all elements in a list of integers.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 10; each integer between 1 and 100.

fields.title: Reverse an Array
fields.description: Reverse the order of elements in a given array.
fields.constraints: Array size between 1 and 100.

fields.title: Find Missing Number
fields.description: Given an array of size n containing numbers from 0 to n, find the missing number.
fields.constraints: Array has exactly one missing number in the range [0, n].

fields.title: Count Occurrences
fields.description: Count the number of times a given element appears in a list.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; elements are integers.

fields.title: Capitalize Each Word
fields.description: Given a sentence, capitalize the first letter of each word.
fields.constraints: Sentence up to 200 characters.

fields.title: Remove Duplicates
fields.description: Remove duplicate elements from a list and return the unique elements in their original order.
fields.constraints: List size between 1 and 100; elements are integers.

fields.title: Intersection of Two Arrays
fields.description: Find the common elements between two arrays.
fields.constraints: Arrays size up to 50; elements are integers.

fields.title: Implement Queue using Stacks
fields.description: Simulate a queue using two stacks. Implement the enqueue and dequeue operations.
fields.constraints: Operations on integer elements.

fields.title: Implement Stack using Queues
fields.description: Simulate a stack using two queues. Implement the push and pop operations.
fields.constraints: Operations on integer elements.

fields.title: Evaluate Postfix Expression
fields.description: Evaluate a postfix (Reverse Polish Notation) expression and return the result.
fields.constraints: Expression contains integers and operators (+, -, *, /) separated by spaces.

fields.title: Longest Common Prefix
fields.description: Given an array of strings, find the longest common prefix among them.
fields.constraints: Array size between 1 and 100, each string up to 100 characters.
